channel.title: Help with rune fusion server
channel.description:
Hey guys, I downloaded rune fusion and the source works great, but before I even edit anything on the client.. I tried to compile and I get this error: [code]TextClass.java:11: cannot find symbol symbol : class Olong location: class TextClass Olong l = 0L; ^ Note: Some input files use unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. 1 error Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
Any help?

item.title: Help with rune fusion server
item.dc:creator: @jaloko jaloko
item.description:
@jaloko wrote:

Yup its telling you that Olong is not a command it can understand. kind of like putting. }Elese not{ its not a command it understands. as the guy above me said. change it to long see what happens.

TextClass.java:11: cannot find symbol symbol : class Olong location: class TextClass Olong l = 0L; ^ Note: Some input files use unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. 1 error Press any key to continue . . .

Any help?[/quote]

remove the “o”

Before: Olong l = 0L; After: long l = 0L;

item.title: Help with rune fusion server
item.dc:creator: @adrian1372 adrian1372
item.description:
@adrian1372 wrote:

Read it, and u will get it… Okay… Something is wrong in your textclass.java file. the error is at line 11. This is a common error. It is often caused by missing symbols,ints or whatever. I think there is a topic posted by a staff member in this section which has a link to a topic with a guide how to fix it. Hope this helps you.
